Here's a PlantUML sequence diagram representing the control flow for the FLibra marketplace application:

```plantuml
@startuml gaiax_fLibra

actor User
participant "Frontend\n(Nuxt.js)" as Frontend
participant "Vuex Store" as Vuex
participant "Firebase\n(Firestore)" as Firebase
participant "Elasticsearch" as ES
participant "IPFS" as IPFS
participant "Ethereum\nSmart Contract" as ETH
participant "Libra Network" as Libra

User -> Frontend : Access marketplace
Frontend -> Vuex : Initialize state
Frontend -> Firebase : Fetch initial data
Firebase --> Frontend : Return data
Frontend -> ES : Perform search
ES --> Frontend : Return search results

User -> Frontend : Create new item listing
Frontend -> IPFS : Upload item image
IPFS --> Frontend : Return image hash
Frontend -> Firebase : Store item details
Firebase -> ES : Trigger item indexing
Frontend -> ETH : Create item in smart contract
ETH --> Frontend : Confirm item creation

User -> Frontend : Purchase item
Frontend -> Libra : Initiate coin transfer
Libra --> Frontend : Confirm transfer
Frontend -> ETH : Update item status
ETH --> Frontend : Confirm status update
Frontend -> Firebase : Update item details
Firebase -> ES : Update search index

User -> Frontend : Leave review
Frontend -> Firebase : Store review
Firebase -> ES : Index review
Frontend -> ETH : Store review hash

Frontend -> Firebase : Listen for changes
Firebase --> Frontend : Push real-time updates
Frontend -> Vuex : Update state
Vuex --> Frontend : Render updated data

@enduml
```